<li class="ref">
<div id="bib13" class="citation"><span class="label">13.</span> <span class="mixed-citation" data-jats-publication-type="other"><span class="person-group" data-jats-person-group-type="author"><span class="string-name"><span class="surname">Kristensson</span>, <span class="given-names">P.O.</span></span>, <span class="string-name"><span class="surname">Lilley</span>, <span class="given-names">J.</span></span>, <span class="string-name"><span class="surname">Black</span>, <span class="given-names">R.</span></span>, and <span class="string-name"><span class="surname">Waller</span>, <span class="given-names">A.</span></span> </span><span class="article-title">A design engineering approach for quantitatively exploring context-aware sentence retrieval for nonspeaking individuals with motor disabilities</span>. In <span class="source"><em>Proceedings of the 2020 CHI Conf. on Human Factors in Computing Systems</em></span>, <span class="year">(2020)</span>, <span class="fpage">1</span>–<span class="lpage">11</span>.</span></div>
